caption: Food was great but the cashier at front was rude and unattentive. Waited 30 min for our food. Talked to one of the older ladies about it, and it turns out the cashier didn’t tell the back staff about our order. Would recommend but change your cashier staff.

The adobo fried rice omelette and lechon kawali was so good! I’m Filipino by the way so I know lol! I guess we got lucky, there’s a review here that said the adobo pizza was luke warm, ours was pretty hot. My friend loved it. I haven’t tried that yet. I like how it’s big, open air with cover and tables are far apart. Great way to social distance.

By far the longest wait of my life. I bought the food at 1156 sat in waited in there eating section until 1249 until my food finally came out mind you only 3 other tables were occupied with people waiting for there food. I WOULD NOT AND I REPEAT NOT RECOMMEND THIS PLACE TO ANYONE!!! My food was cold and was just ok. Def not worth the wait. If I could give zero stars I would.

Let me start by saying my husband is half Filipino so we had somewhat high expectations and were excited to try this place. I think they might be short staffed, or at least it seemed like it tonight. When we arrived there were no other customers so we were a little surprised by a 20 minute wait for the food. While we were waiting for our food it began to get busy. I ordered the adobo pizza just to try something different and it was luke warm. My first bite had a piece of chicken with bone which was an unfortunate surprise. It's definitely a creative take on adobo. The taste was okay, but I wouldn't order it again. My husband had the plantation breakfast with the ube pancakes and we had halo halo for dessert. The winners of this experience were the ube pancakes and the halo halo. Maybe other menu items are better and maybe we came on the wrong day, but I'm not sure if we will return.
